{{Infobox protected area | name = Big Shoals State Park | iucn_category = III | map = Florida | map_caption = | location = [[Hamilton County, Florida]], USA | nearest_city = [[White Springs, Florida]] | coordinates = {{coords|30|20|21|N|82|40|59|W|region:US-FL|display=inline, title}} | area = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = [[Florida Department of Environmental Protection]] }}
'''Big Shoals State Park''' in [[Hamilton County, Florida]]<ref>[http://www.floridastateparks.org/bigshoals/ Big Shoals State Park] Florida State Park</ref> is a [[Florida State Parks|Florida State Park]]. It is approximately {{convert|1|mi|km|spell=in}} east of [[White Springs, Florida|White Springs]], off [[U.S. Route 41 in Florida|US 41]]. The park is situated on the [[Suwannee River]] and features Limestone bluffs as well as the biggest whitewater rapids in all of Florida. The park also features more than {{convert|28|mi|km}} of hiking and nature trails, and freshwater fishing.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://jacksonville.com/sports/2017-04-19/bob-mcnally-s-outdoors-outlook |title=Bob McNally’s Outdoors Outlook |work=jacksonville.com |access-date=April 21, 2017}}</ref>
