'''''The Evolution of Melanism: a study of recurring necessity; with special reference to [[industrial melanism]] in the Lepidoptera''''' is a 1973 science [[book]] by the [[lepidopterist]] [[Bernard Kettlewell]].

The book includes Kettlewell's original papers in the journal ''[[Heredity (journal)|Heredity]]'' on his classic [[predator|predation]] experiments on the [[peppered moth]]. It also covers Kettlewell's experiments in the [[Hebrides]].

